.TH "lpfc_bg_scsi_prep_dma_buf" 9 "lpfc_bg_scsi_prep_dma_buf" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
lpfc_bg_scsi_prep_dma_buf \- Wrapper function for DMA mapping of scsi buffer using BlockGuard.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" lpfc_bg_scsi_prep_dma_buf
.BI "(struct lpfc_hba *phba "  ","
.BI "struct lpfc_io_buf *lpfc_cmd "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "phba" 12
The Hba for which this call is being executed.
.IP "lpfc_cmd" 12
The scsi buffer which is going to be mapped.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This routine wraps the actual DMA mapping function pointer from the
lpfc_hba struct.

Return codes:
1 - Error
0 - Success
